            example with a stated answer (p.4-124, "TDM = 2 ... 5 times bigger than the PKP level
            ... will not occur before 2.59 s"). Three representations agree: prose 2.59, table 2.593,
            equation 2.5934.
            VERIFY PHASE PROVEN BEFORE THE ENGINE EXISTS: recomputed all 210 published cells from the
            published equation + constants. 210/210 agree, worst error 0.135%, which is the table's
            own rounding to 3 decimals.
            ⚠ THE TOLERANCE QUESTION IS ANSWERED, AND THE ANSWER IS "NO NUMBER NEEDED." Reproducing a
            published TABLE is arithmetic; the pass criterion is the table's printed precision. SEL's
            +/-1.5 cycles / +/-4% spec measures a PHYSICAL relay against its own curve, which is an
            honesty note for the app, NOT the gate. Nothing was invented, so nothing is theatre.
            🔴 THE TOOL MUST NOT CLAIM "IMPLEMENTS IEEE C37.112". GE and SEL BOTH cite C37.112-1996,
            in their own words, over DIFFERENT constants, and C37.112 is gated and unread. Measured
            the divergence rather than eyeballing it: ~5x apart, and the ratio is FLAT for Moderately
            and Very Inverse (same shape, different time dial convention) but DRIFTS 4.95 -> 3.89 for
            Extremely Inverse (a genuinely different SHAPE). SEL's own footnote independently flags
            that same row as the outlier. Mixing the two tables silently = trip times wrong by 5x.
            This is 01's tier rule firing on a new subject: name the manufacturer family, cite the
            manual, claim no standards conformance.
            Lesson earned the hard way: two independent research passes each scraped SEL's Table 9.3
